====Hyphenation====
:meta&middot;phor

===Etymology===
From the Latin and Greek ''metaphora'', the transferring of the meaning of one word to another word.<!--the Greek should be in Greek alphabet-->

===Noun===
'''metaphor''' (''plural'' '''metaphors''')

#A [[figure of speech]] in which a word or phrase is used to refer to something that it isn't, implying a similarity between the word or phrase used and the thing described, and without the words "like" or "as".  Compare [[simile]].

